00:13:55,184 --> 00:13:57,652
or a hearse?

266
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:59,320
They'll be fine.

267
00:13:59,388 --> 00:14:03,523
Why don't you, uh, tell me
what you're looking for?

268
00:14:10,966 --> 00:14:12,127
(laughing):
The doll…

269
00:14:12,167 --> 00:14:15,370
Uh, it's pink and it opens up

270
00:14:15,438 --> 00:14:17,572
and there's teeny furniture,

271
00:14:17,639 --> 00:14:21,075
and you put the boy doll
on top of the girl doll

272
00:14:21,143 --> 00:14:23,010
and we learn about urges.

273
00:14:26,415 --> 00:14:29,316
What's her name?

274
00:14:29,385 --> 00:14:31,753
Rebecca—
she told you.

275
00:14:31,820 --> 00:14:32,754
Really?

276
00:14:32,821 --> 00:14:34,405
How do you
know Rebecca?

277
00:14:34,423 --> 00:14:36,218
We've been married
for seven years.

278
00:14:36,258 --> 00:14:37,958
(chuckles)

279
00:14:38,025 --> 00:14:39,321
So that's your fantasy?

280
00:14:39,361 --> 00:14:42,830
All the money in the world,
the most elaborate,

281
00:14:42,898 --> 00:14:45,160
high-class underground
operation ever designed,

282
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,735
and you just want
to play house?

283
00:14:47,803 --> 00:14:49,565
I guess the rich
really are different.

284
00:14:49,605 --> 00:14:50,932
Why, what's your fantasy?

285
00:14:50,972 --> 00:14:53,001
Oh, I'm okay right here
in the real world, thanks.

286
00:14:53,041 --> 00:14:55,376
Oh, don't, no,
you have a fantasy.

287
00:14:55,444 --> 00:14:56,744
Okay, we all do.

288
00:14:56,812 --> 00:14:58,073
We need it to survive,

289
00:14:58,113 --> 00:15:00,615
and I think your fantasy

290
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:13,461
But then

291
00:15:13,529 --> 00:15:16,565
the brave little F.B.I. agent
whisked her away

292
00:15:16,598 --> 00:15:17,659
from the cash-wielding losers

293
00:15:17,699 --> 00:15:20,468
and restored
her true identity,

294
00:15:20,536 --> 00:15:23,571
and she fell in love with him.

295
00:15:23,639 --> 00:15:24,899
It doesn't go like that.

296
00:15:24,939 --> 00:15:27,202
(scoffing):
I saw how you were with her.

297
00:15:27,242 --> 00:15:29,544
It was,
it was almost cute.

298
00:15:29,611 --> 00:15:31,373
We're not here to talk about me.
Hey,

299
00:15:31,413 --> 00:15:33,274
I don't have to be here at all.

300
00:15:33,314 --> 00:15:35,478
I mean, you're not going
to arrest me.

301
00:15:35,518 --> 00:15:38,553
Pretty sure you're not going
to kill me, so…

302
00:15:38,620 --> 00:15:42,089
If we're going to talk,
we're both going to talk.

303
00:15:42,157 --> 00:15:46,994
I mean, she,
she changed things for you.

304
00:15:47,062 --> 00:15:51,766
So you're the head
of this F.B.I. task force

305
00:15:51,834 --> 00:15:55,102
to uncover the Dollhouse,

306
00:15:55,170 --> 00:15:57,399
and you're working hard,
you're chasing leads,

307
00:15:57,439 --> 00:16:01,709
you're cracking skulls,
but it's just work.

308
00:16:10,586 --> 00:16:11,752
And suddenly…

309
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:12,753
(cork pops)

310
00:16:12,821 --> 00:16:15,389
it gets personal.

311
00:16:20,161 --> 00:16:23,396
Tell me you haven't
thought about it.

312
00:16:23,465 --> 00:16:25,093
You know, her,
her grateful tears,

313
00:16:25,133 --> 00:16:30,037
her, her welcoming embrace,
her warm breath.

314
00:16:30,105 --> 00:16:32,006
Are you married?

315
00:16:32,073 --> 00:16:33,107
Was.

316
00:16:33,174 --> 00:16:34,107
Oh,

317
00:16:34,175 --> 00:16:35,275
That's…

318
00:16:35,343 --> 00:16:37,673
Is there someone
in your life right now?

319
00:16:37,713 --> 00:16:39,646
This is getting old.

320
00:16:39,715 --> 00:16:40,948
Of course not.

321
00:16:41,016 --> 00:16:43,178
No, there's no room
for a real girl, is there,

322
00:16:43,218 --> 00:16:44,986
when you can feel

323
00:16:45,053 --> 00:16:47,622
Caroline beckoning?

324
00:16:47,689 --> 00:16:51,353
(chuckling): You know, I have to say
I-I think your fantasy

325
00:16:51,393 --> 00:16:53,761
is even sadder than mine.

326
00:16:53,829 --> 00:16:55,190
Won't know until I hear it.

327
00:16:55,230 --> 00:16:56,163
Well,

328
00:16:56,230 --> 00:17:00,467
it didn't involve
drinking alone.

329
00:17:11,446 --> 00:17:12,674
Sierra is different.

330
00:17:12,714 --> 00:17:14,381
How is she different?

331
00:17:14,449 --> 00:17:17,785
I'm sorry.

332
00:17:17,854 --> 00:17:19,887
Victor,

333
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:23,189
do you remember being in
the showers with Sierra?

334
00:17:23,225 --> 00:17:25,993
You were watching her?

335
00:17:26,061 --> 00:17:28,262
How does Sierra make you feel?

336
00:17:30,298 --> 00:17:33,034
Better.

337
00:17:33,102 --> 00:17:34,830
I can't believe this.
I'm filling in

338
00:17:34,870 --> 00:17:37,499
for Ramirez for a week and
my active invents rape?

339
00:17:37,539 --> 00:17:39,535
We don't know
what happened yet.

340
00:17:39,575 --> 00:17:41,437
Victor might have just
triggered a memory.

341
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:43,410
Well, Hearn's
out for blood.

342
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:45,774
Hearn hasn't found
anything on the tapes.

343
00:17:45,814 --> 00:17:47,448
Nobody has.

344
00:17:47,515 --> 00:17:48,877
How is that
even possible?

345
00:17:48,917 --> 00:17:50,612
Every square inch of
this place is monitored.

346
00:17:50,652 --> 00:17:53,754
If two actives
are going at it…

347
00:17:53,822 --> 00:17:56,390
What do you think
DeWitt'll do?

348
00:17:56,458 --> 00:17:58,570
You think she'll
come down hard?

349
00:17:58,860 --> 00:18:00,906
It was probably
just a mistake.

350
00:18:11,406 --> 00:18:12,707
They're all broken.

351
00:18:18,914 --> 00:18:22,583
Rebecca was amazing.

352
00:18:22,650 --> 00:18:25,753
She was a nurse and…

353
00:18:25,821 --> 00:18:27,049
(laughing):
I was a basket case,

354
00:18:27,089 --> 00:18:30,124
So, you know,
not a, not a bad match.

355
00:18:30,191 --> 00:18:32,927
I was the guy
with the almost great idea—

356
00:18:32,995 --> 00:18:38,100
floogle
and blahoo! And facebooger.

357
00:18:38,166 --> 00:18:41,502
I was, I was just always
one step behind,

358
00:18:41,569 --> 00:18:43,638
and she was cool with it.

359
00:18:43,705 --> 00:18:45,667
And did she look
exactly like Caroline?

360
00:18:45,707 --> 00:18:47,775
No, but—

361
00:18:47,843 --> 00:18:51,879
Eat it, f-bitch-I—
she was beautiful

362
00:18:51,947 --> 00:18:54,414
and she knew it
and she loved me.

363
00:18:54,482 --> 00:18:56,117
I mean, I had been…

364
00:18:56,184 --> 00:18:58,446
(sighing):
I had been given a gift.

365
00:18:58,486 --> 00:19:01,521
And now you're hiring zombies.

366
00:19:11,266 --> 00:19:12,732
Place is empty.

367
00:19:12,801 --> 00:19:14,068
Shame— big place.

368
00:19:14,136 --> 00:19:15,069
(scoffs)

369
00:19:15,137 --> 00:19:16,403
This place.

370
00:19:16,471 --> 00:19:18,500
This place could fit
in my bathroom.

371
00:19:18,540 --> 00:19:21,003
I mean, this place could fit
in my guest bathroom.

372
00:19:21,043 --> 00:19:22,009
All right?

373
00:19:22,077 --> 00:19:23,672
I mean, I finally got
one step ahead.

374
00:19:23,712 --> 00:19:25,412
“Bouncy the Rat.”

375
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:26,774
Kids love it.
Ooh, they do.

376
00:19:26,814 --> 00:19:30,686
I mean,
long story still kind of long,

377
00:19:30,752 --> 00:19:34,254
my first check had more zeros
than the Luftwaffe.

378
00:19:34,322 --> 00:19:35,255
The Japanese—

379
00:19:35,323 --> 00:19:38,559
They had the Zeros,
not the Germans.

380
00:19:38,626 --> 00:19:40,260
(sighs)

381
00:19:40,328 --> 00:19:41,662
It was money.

382
00:19:41,730 --> 00:19:43,591
All right, it was
roll-around-in money

383
00:19:43,631 --> 00:19:45,299
and Rebecca had no idea.

384
00:19:45,366 --> 00:19:47,262
She'd been supporting
the both of us for years.

385
00:19:47,302 --> 00:19:48,496
I mean ridiculous hours.

386
00:19:48,536 --> 00:19:50,065
We were living
in a one-room shack,

387
00:19:50,105 --> 00:19:53,140
and I knew this house
was exactly her type.

388
00:19:53,208 --> 00:19:56,477
I paid cash and I called her up.

389
00:19:56,544 --> 00:19:58,473
I said,
“meet me at this address,

390
00:19:58,513 --> 00:19:59,474
it's really important,”

391
00:19:59,514 --> 00:20:01,494
and she was worried,
you know,

392
00:20:10,592 --> 00:20:13,961
thinking about the look
on her face

393
00:20:14,029 --> 00:20:16,630
when she saw this place

394
00:20:16,698 --> 00:20:19,466
and I told her it was ours.

395
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:27,407
Sanitation truck…

396
00:20:27,475 --> 00:20:30,111
sideswiped her car…

397
00:20:30,178 --> 00:20:33,413
three blocks from here,

398
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:38,219
and I heard the impact and…
(sighs)

399
00:20:38,286 --> 00:20:41,188
they said it was quick.

400
00:20:41,256 --> 00:20:46,061
I guess that, you know,
they always have to say that.

401
00:20:46,128 --> 00:20:48,528
Right?

402
00:20:48,596 --> 00:20:52,199
But she never got
to see this house,

403
00:20:52,268 --> 00:20:55,870
and she never knew I made good.

404
00:20:55,938 --> 00:21:00,641
So every year on this date,

405
00:21:12,854 --> 00:21:15,489
And then you sleep with her.

406
00:21:15,556 --> 00:21:17,958
It is a fantasy.

407
00:21:18,025 --> 00:21:21,262
I'm sorry for your
loss, Mr Mynor.

408
00:21:21,329 --> 00:21:24,524
It doesn't make you anything
other than a predator.

409
00:21:24,564 --> 00:21:27,796
Well, I'm sure I'm in need of
some serious moral spankitude,

410
00:21:27,836 --> 00:21:32,039
but, uh, guess who's not
qualified to be my rabbi.

411
00:21:32,107 --> 00:21:34,870
Well, I'm perfectly happy
to let a federal judge…

412
00:21:34,910 --> 00:21:36,304
Throw you in jail, hmm?

413
00:21:36,344 --> 00:21:39,880
I mean, we got trespassing,
we got assault,

414
00:21:39,948 --> 00:21:42,244
<i>and what you've
got is a girl</i>

415
00:21:42,284 --> 00:21:43,411
you're obsessed with,

416
00:21:43,451 --> 00:21:47,087
who I think we can both agree
is not here.

417
00:21:47,155 --> 00:21:49,384
I mean, this is not
“beat up the geek,” big guy.

418
00:21:49,424 --> 00:21:51,485
This is
the internet establishment.

419
00:21:51,525 --> 00:21:55,022
<i>You put me in front of a judge,
he'll take you down.</i>

420
00:21:55,062 --> 00:21:56,892
He'll throw the Kindle at you.

421
00:21:56,932 --> 00:21:59,232
(siren wailing)

422
00:21:59,301 --> 00:22:02,036
(chuckling):
Oh… Oh.

423
00:22:11,746 --> 00:22:14,242
You might not be punished
and I might not be alive,

424
00:22:14,282 --> 00:22:15,844
but this house will fall.

425
00:22:15,884 --> 00:22:19,753
The first hurdle
in my business is the people

426
00:22:19,821 --> 00:22:22,350
who will not accept the change
that's already happened.

427
00:22:22,390 --> 00:22:23,623
Go.

428
00:22:23,691 --> 00:22:26,426
Go live in
your real world.

429
00:22:26,494 --> 00:22:29,296
If you ever did.

430
00:22:33,034 --> 00:22:35,035
Happy anniversary.

431
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:43,434
If you could have somebody be
the perfect person,

432
00:22:43,703 --> 00:22:47,927
the moment you wish for that you
know you're never going to get,

433
00:22:47,941 --> 00:22:50,376
and someone signed on
to do that,

434
00:22:50,444 --> 00:22:53,946
to help you…

435
00:22:54,014 --> 00:22:57,616
I think that could be okay.

436
00:22:57,684 --> 00:23:02,188
I think that could be
maybe beautiful.

437
00:23:57,777 --> 00:24:00,413
This is Boyd Langton
for Mr Dominic.

438
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:22,701
I did something bad.

439
00:24:22,770 --> 00:24:24,903
What did you do?

440
00:24:24,971 --> 00:24:27,739
Nobody will tell me.

441
00:24:27,807 --> 00:24:29,341
Victor, I need you

442
00:24:29,409 --> 00:24:30,771
to come with me, please.

443
00:24:30,811 --> 00:24:32,078
Where?

444
00:24:32,145 --> 00:24:34,455
I need you to come
with me, please.

445
00:24:39,286 --> 00:24:41,134
Why did Sierra scream at me?

446
00:24:42,655 --> 00:24:44,990
Bicks:
Who authorized this?

447
00:24:45,059 --> 00:24:46,219
I didn't rape
the doll.

448
00:24:46,259 --> 00:24:49,061
Lawrence, Lawrence,
I didn't do this.

449
00:24:49,129 --> 00:24:50,190
You know me, man.

450
00:24:50,230 --> 00:24:51,324
I wouldn't do this, man.

451
00:24:51,364 --> 00:24:52,792
Come on, you know
I didn't do this!

452
00:24:52,832 --> 00:24:54,100
I didn't do this!

453
00:24:54,167 --> 00:24:55,995
Where are they
taking Victor?

454
00:24:56,035 --> 00:24:58,304
Why don't you go
paint something?

455
00:24:58,371 --> 00:24:59,805
Nice work, man.

456
00:25:10,250 --> 00:25:11,917
Not anymore.

457
00:25:11,985 --> 00:25:13,113
Mellie:
Is this enough?

458
00:25:13,153 --> 00:25:14,354
Thanks.

459
00:25:18,992 --> 00:25:21,054
Are you, uh, always
gonna show up bleeding?

460
00:25:21,094 --> 00:25:22,744
'cause it's kind
of funny

461
00:25:22,762 --> 00:25:24,863
how I'm not
getting used to it.

462
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,168
It was her.

463
00:25:29,236 --> 00:25:30,902
You met Caroline?

464
00:25:30,970 --> 00:25:32,238
I saw Caroline.

465
00:25:32,305 --> 00:25:33,572
I met Rebecca.

466
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,469
And I let both of
them get away.

467
00:25:35,509 --> 00:25:36,809
So, it's all true.

468
00:25:36,876 --> 00:25:38,071
I knew it was true.

469
00:25:38,111 --> 00:25:40,212
I just didn't expect…

470
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:42,041
If it had been
anybody else,

471
00:25:42,081 --> 00:25:43,543
the jail cells
would be full,

472
00:25:43,583 --> 00:25:46,279
and I'd be busy writing the
great American arrest report.

473
00:25:46,319 --> 00:25:47,814
I never thought
it would be her.

474
00:25:47,854 --> 00:25:49,174
Did you get the guy?

475
00:25:49,189 --> 00:25:51,423
The… John,
the… client.

476
00:25:51,491 --> 00:25:52,877
What are they called?

477
00:25:54,194 --> 00:25:55,461
I talked to him.

478
00:25:55,529 --> 00:25:56,962
And?

479
00:26:11,110 --> 00:26:12,378
I'm sorry.

480
00:26:12,445 --> 00:26:14,079
I'm not.

481
00:26:14,146 --> 00:26:15,548
I mean, I am.

482
00:26:15,615 --> 00:26:16,982
I-I mean, you are.

483
00:26:17,050 --> 00:26:18,116
Don't do that.

484
00:26:18,186 --> 00:26:19,912
Don't inflate the stock
before you dump it.

485
00:26:19,952 --> 00:26:21,587
Uh…

486
00:26:21,655 --> 00:26:24,990
Don't think about her
and kiss me.

487
00:26:25,058 --> 00:26:27,159
I wasn't, uh…

488
00:26:27,227 --> 00:26:28,895
Forget it.

489
00:26:28,961 --> 00:26:31,029
I think it's best
we forget it.

490
00:26:31,097 --> 00:26:32,125
Would be stupid, anyway.

491
00:26:32,165 --> 00:26:34,533
We're neighbors,
we should just…

492
00:26:34,601 --> 00:26:35,862
we should be
neighborly.

493
00:26:35,902 --> 00:26:36,835
Great.

494
00:26:36,903 --> 00:26:37,836
Yes.

495
00:26:37,904 --> 00:26:38,970
Neighborly.

496
00:26:39,038 --> 00:26:40,433
Can I borrow
a cup of sugar?

497
00:26:40,473 --> 00:26:41,507
(both laughing)

498
00:26:41,575 --> 00:26:43,809
Like that.

499
00:26:43,876 --> 00:26:47,312
So, why don't you tell me
about today.

500
00:26:49,316 --> 00:26:51,584
The guy's name was Joel Mynor.

501
00:26:52,852 --> 00:26:55,360
<i>Joel Mynor from
Bouncy the Rat?</i>

502
00:27:32,158 --> 00:27:33,992
Do you trust me?

503
00:27:34,061 --> 00:27:35,861
With my life.

504
00:27:35,928 --> 00:27:37,842
Do you want to play the game?

505
00:27:39,832 --> 00:27:41,400
No.

506
00:27:41,468 --> 00:27:46,505
But you remember to be very
quiet during the game, right?

507
00:27:46,573 --> 00:27:49,308
Noise is upsetting.

508
00:27:50,343 --> 00:27:51,777
Lift up your dress.

509
00:27:59,786 --> 00:28:01,520
That wasn't quiet.

510
00:28:11,431 --> 00:28:13,543
He had to be flush
with success,

511
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:15,462
or he'd never
have tried again.

512
00:28:15,502 --> 00:28:17,230
You will never take
action like that

513
00:28:17,270 --> 00:28:18,931
on your own again
inside these walls.

514
00:28:18,971 --> 00:28:19,905
Am I clear?

515
00:28:19,972 --> 00:28:22,541
You're clear.

516
00:28:22,609 --> 00:28:24,971
A bonus has been wired
to your account.

517
00:28:25,011 --> 00:28:27,379
I don't need a bonus.

518
00:28:28,948 --> 00:28:31,049
Well, I need to give it to you.

519
00:28:31,117 --> 00:28:32,584
That's all.

520
00:28:34,821 --> 00:28:36,655
Ms Dewitt.

521
00:28:40,794 --> 00:28:43,028
(sighs)

522
00:28:46,666 --> 00:28:47,894
What do we do with Hearn?

523
00:28:47,934 --> 00:28:50,168
I'll let you know.

524
00:28:50,236 --> 00:28:53,271
And you saw the other
thing, the tap?

525
00:28:55,408 --> 00:28:56,835
<i>Joel Mynor from Bouncy the Rat?</i>

526
00:28:56,875 --> 00:28:59,251
<i>He was on the cover of Wired.</i>

527
00:29:10,922 --> 00:29:13,926
Do you have an
exit strategy?

528
00:29:13,992 --> 00:29:17,027
We have a handler
abusing an active,

529
00:29:17,096 --> 00:29:19,460
a federal agent
interrupting an engagement,

530
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:22,272
