602
00:33:48,330 --> 00:33:49,930
You think I'm
gonna beg?

603
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:51,226
You want to kill me?

604
00:33:51,266 --> 00:33:52,862
You want to put me in the attic?

605
00:33:52,902 --> 00:33:54,570
I can't stop you.

606
00:33:54,637 --> 00:33:56,404
The jig is up.

607
00:33:56,471 --> 00:33:57,461
How many times?

608
00:33:57,473 --> 00:33:59,406
(panting)

609
00:33:59,475 --> 00:34:02,577
I can find out, but I want
to hear it from you.

610
00:34:10,619 --> 00:34:12,048
it makes it better
because she thinks

611
00:34:12,088 --> 00:34:13,815
she's in love for
all of a day?

612
00:34:13,855 --> 00:34:15,585
We're in the business
of using people.

613
00:34:15,625 --> 00:34:17,720
You understand less about
this business than you think.

614
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:20,323
And you don't get how it
actually works down there.

615
00:34:20,363 --> 00:34:22,091
You put a bunch
of stone foxes

616
00:34:22,131 --> 00:34:23,593
with no willpower
and no memory

617
00:34:23,633 --> 00:34:25,398
running around naked.

618
00:34:25,467 --> 00:34:27,997
Did you think this
wouldn't ever happen?

619
00:34:28,037 --> 00:34:30,939
Did it make it better?

620
00:34:31,006 --> 00:34:33,607
That she didn't struggle?

621
00:34:33,676 --> 00:34:35,211
No.

622
00:34:35,277 --> 00:34:37,578
It made it easier.

623
00:34:38,646 --> 00:34:40,692
Mr Dominic, would you leave us?

624
00:34:41,449 --> 00:34:42,684
Ms Dewitt, I…

625
00:34:42,752 --> 00:34:43,814
I'll be perfectly safe.

626
00:34:43,854 --> 00:34:45,719
Please.

627
00:34:49,959 --> 00:34:51,788
<i>We are in the business
of using people.</i>

628
00:34:51,828 --> 00:34:56,363
The question is,
what is the best use

629
00:34:56,430 --> 00:34:58,432
for someone like you?

630
00:35:11,047 --> 00:35:12,281
really.

631
00:35:12,348 --> 00:35:15,011
I need her killed,
and it can't be clean.

632
00:35:15,051 --> 00:35:17,413
This is your chance
to avoid the attic.

633
00:35:17,453 --> 00:35:20,889
You may even consider it
something of a promotion.

634
00:35:20,957 --> 00:35:22,523
After all,

635
00:35:22,590 --> 00:35:24,225
this one will…

636
00:35:24,293 --> 00:35:26,395
probably struggle.

637
00:35:27,529 --> 00:35:29,531
(breathing heavily, moaning)

638
00:35:47,617 --> 00:35:49,482
My God.

639
00:35:49,551 --> 00:35:51,520
You're so…

640
00:35:51,586 --> 00:35:53,188
Neighborly.

641
00:35:53,254 --> 00:35:55,555
(both chuckling)

642
00:35:55,625 --> 00:35:57,658
So…

643
00:35:57,727 --> 00:35:59,793
Can I borrow a
cup of sugar?

644
00:35:59,863 --> 00:36:01,162
(laughing)

645
00:36:12,875 --> 00:36:15,211
(groaning)

646
00:36:17,012 --> 00:36:19,814
I'm not gonna
freak out on you.

647
00:36:19,883 --> 00:36:22,350
Uh… good.

648
00:36:22,418 --> 00:36:24,314
When you tell me this
is all a mistake

649
00:36:24,354 --> 00:36:25,780
and we should forget
it ever happened,

650
00:36:25,820 --> 00:36:27,521
I'm gonna be very cool.

651
00:36:27,590 --> 00:36:30,362
You're gonna be bothered
by how cool I am.

652
00:36:31,793 --> 00:36:33,461
What if I don't say that?

653
00:36:33,527 --> 00:36:34,655
I'll still be cool,

654
00:36:34,695 --> 00:36:37,064
<i>But not as cool.</i>

655
00:36:37,133 --> 00:36:39,628
<i>What if you tell me
it was a mistake?</i>

656
00:36:39,668 --> 00:36:42,170
Oh, God, you're
gonna be so clingy,

657
00:36:42,238 --> 00:36:43,492
weeping and moping,

658
00:36:43,539 --> 00:36:44,840
texting me.

659
00:36:44,906 --> 00:36:46,235
It's too embarrassing.

660
00:36:46,275 --> 00:36:48,538
I am not a piece of meat,
you know.

661
00:36:48,578 --> 00:36:50,360
I have a heart.
(chuckling)

662
00:36:51,246 --> 00:36:53,248
Blah, blah.

663
00:36:58,688 --> 00:37:01,621
I was thinking
about Caroline.

664
00:37:10,199 --> 00:37:12,128
I think what they're
doing is wrong.

665
00:37:12,168 --> 00:37:14,128
And I don't love seeing
you get beat up

666
00:37:14,168 --> 00:37:16,104
and shot, but…

667
00:37:16,172 --> 00:37:18,218
I think your work
is important.

668
00:37:20,375 --> 00:37:22,344
Then help me out.

669
00:37:22,410 --> 00:37:25,374
Is this the part where you
dress me up and use me as bait?

670
00:37:25,414 --> 00:37:27,724
'cause those movies
never end well.

671
00:37:29,984 --> 00:37:32,780
It's the part where I run
down to Tiki Port

672
00:37:32,820 --> 00:37:35,756
and grab us dinner
and we go over my files

673
00:37:35,824 --> 00:37:38,452
and you give me your
perspective on some stuff.

674
00:37:38,492 --> 00:37:40,428
Might see something
I didn't.

675
00:37:40,496 --> 00:37:42,262
You think I'd be helpful?

676
00:37:42,332 --> 00:37:43,932
Yeah.

677
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:46,962
That's the sweetest thing
you've done for me all day.

678
00:37:47,002 --> 00:37:48,938
Well…

679
00:37:49,004 --> 00:37:51,439
What about the,
um…

680
00:37:51,506 --> 00:37:53,441
the other things?
(chuckles)

681
00:37:53,508 --> 00:37:55,375
Fetch me spring rolls.

682
00:37:55,445 --> 00:37:59,146
Then we'll bust this case
wide open.

683
00:37:59,215 --> 00:38:02,184
(distant traffic noise,
horns honking)

684
00:38:33,148 --> 00:38:34,883
Whoever you are,

685
00:38:34,949 --> 00:38:36,745
I swear I don't want
to hurt you.

686
00:38:36,785 --> 00:38:38,354
I know.

687
00:38:38,420 --> 00:38:40,154
(groans)

688
00:38:42,691 --> 00:38:44,225
I'm counting on it.

689
00:38:47,610 --> 00:38:49,524
You think it's not happening?

690
00:38:49,570 --> 00:38:52,540
<i>You think they're not controlling you?</i>

691
00:38:52,826 --> 00:38:54,120
Don't worry about it.

692
00:38:54,160 --> 00:38:56,129
Just sit back

693
00:38:56,197 --> 00:38:59,064
and wait for them to tell you
what to buy.

694
00:38:59,133 --> 00:39:01,535
(groans)

695
